That is nothing new for the United States, neither for the entire world.
The fact that you can make a compact with what was in the past called a territory is not only done by the United States, it is around the world.
When the United States came to Puerto Rico in 1898, we had a special arrangement with Spain.
We were Spaniard citizens.
We had autonomy.
The special charter could only be amended if the people of Puerto Rico will accept it--in a sense, basically the same concept we want right now to clarify.
